               <p>THOMAS WOODWARD. I am a <rs id="t18320405-263-viclabel1545" type="occupation">grocer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-263-victim2234 t18320405-263-viclabel1545"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18320405-263-crimeloc1546">Piccadilly</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-263-crimeloc1546" type="placeName" value="Piccadilly"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-263-crimeloc1546" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-263-off1543 t18320405-263-crimeloc1546"></join> - the prisoner was my <rs id="t18320405-263-deflabel1547" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-263-defend2232 t18320405-263-deflabel1547"></join> for some weeks. On the 7th of March, about seven o'clock, I found a piece of soap on him - he had hidden it, and my young man found it, and marked it with the letters T. N. - I found it on him, with the mark; I sent for the officer, and gave him in charge - I went to his lodging, but did not go up stairs - I missed some knives and forks, and some tea and other things.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-263-person2235">
                  THOMAS 
                  FARRANT
               <interp inst="t18320405-263-person2235" type="surname" value="FARRANT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-263-person2235" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-263-person2235" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable C 42.) I received the prisoner at the watch-house; I went to the house, where I saw his mother - he had directed me there; I there got these two knives, this fork, and 1 lb. 11 ozs. of black and green tea; I mentioned it to the prisoner the next morning, and he said he had taken the knives and fork,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183204050110"></xptr>but not the tea; I said the bag of tea was marked, and he said that was since I took it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My master used to beat me with a broom, and broke it in three pieces about my arms.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-263-person2236">
                  THOMAS 
                  WOODWARD
               <interp inst="t18320405-263-person2236" type="surname" value="WOODWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-263-person2236" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-263-person2236" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He was endeavouring to run away from me, and I got a broom-stick and hit him three times, to prevent it - I had a good character with him.</p>
